@NODE Setup_e "Setting the Golden Gate Card"
              @{b} SETTING THE GOLDEN GATE CARD @{ub}

GoldenGate-386SX/486SLC/486SLC2 and different Amiga models:
-----------------------------------------------------------

GoldenGate has to know if it runs on an A2000, A3000 or A4000. For some
reasons there is no unique mechanism for software running on an Amiga
to recognize the current machine type. In the case that GolenGate's build
in detection fails there is a separate way to tell the emulator the
type of your Amiga. To do this you have to create a textfile named
glib.cnf in the DEVS drawer of your boot device. (e.g. by means of ED).
This textfile contains just a single word:

   machine_Ax000     where    x=2 for Amiga A2000
                              x=3 for Amiga A3000
                              x=4 for Amiga A4000

You can check the autodetection of GoldenGate by starting GG directly from
the CLI with the option INFO. To do so change to the drawer GoldenGate and
type

   GG INFO


GoldenGate and HIMEM.SYS:
-------------------------

If you use your GoldenGate-386SX with 512kB local ram (delivery state)
and you use amiga memory as extended memory you have to modifiy the
HIMEM.SYS entry in the file CONFIG.SYS as follows:

device={path}HIMEM.SYS /machine:2

where {path} is the full pathname of the subdirectory where HIMEM.SYS
is located, e.g.

      {path} = C:\DOS\

GoldenGate and EMM386.EXE or QEMM386.SYS:
-----------------------------------------

If you want to use EMM386.EXE or QEMM386.SYS you have to activate
SMARTDRV.EXE before. Otherwise the system will crash if there is a disk IO
into the UMA. (which happens e.g. with deviceHigh, lh or LoadHigh etc.)


The Jumper J4 and J5 on the GoldenGate board
--------------------------------------------
The Jumpers J4 and J5 on the GoldenGate board are not used at the moment
and must not be closed therefore.


The Format-command in GoldenGate Server mode
--------------------------------------------
With the different Workbench-versions several FORMAT commands have been
delivered, which do not support the Server mode of the GoldenGate properly.
We strongly recommend to use the Format command from the system drawer
of the Goldmine I disk. This makes sure, that your drives work fine in
the Server mode.


Installation of additional Amiga harddisk partitions via HDT.SYS
----------------------------------------------------------------

Golden Gate supports more than two harddisks in PC-mode via the hdt.sys
driver. Please refer to the Golden Gate manual for more informations
about the installation of hdt.sys and the format utility PFormat.

Additional, hdt.sys driven partitions have the following limitations:

- The size of each logical drive is limited to 32 MBytes. If the Amiga
partition is bigger, PFormat uses only 32 MBytes for the PC partition.

- HDT.SYS does not work if two AT-Bus harddisks are already present or
if you use a PC-SCSI controller with two harddisk drives.

- HDT.SYS does not work in the virtual PC mode. The hdt.sys driver does
not work together with EMM386.EXE, QEMM and similar drivers. It is not
possible to access the partitions in Windows 3.0/3.1 enhanced mode, too.


Compatibility with the Adaptec 1542C
------------------------------------

The actual version of the Golden Gate software supports the new Adaptec
1542C controller. Earlier versions ot the GG software do not! You have
to disable the floppy controller option on the Adaptec via Dip-switch 5,
because the floppy controller is not compatible with the Golden Gate
board. To access PC-floppy drives, you should use the vortex FDC-Kit.


The Task utility on the Goldmine II disk
----------------------------------------

Syntax: TASK [ON:nn] [OFF:mm]
        nn=Task On-Time
        mm=Task Off-Time
        (Unit = 1/50 seconds)

With the Task utility the task priority of the GoldenGate can be adjusted
to the requirements of your applications. A lower priority for GoldenGate
means more computing time and performance on the Amiga side.
The on-time defines the time the GoldenGate can access the Amiga
resources without limitations. In the off-time interval, the GoldenGate
stops its activities to speed up the Amigasystem. The off/on-time settings
are independed. Default is off-time 0, GoldenGate consumes all free
processor time. Recommendation: values between 0...5


Use of PC floppy disk drives together with the video emulation
--------------------------------------------------------------
The use of PC floppy disk drives which are connected with the GoldenGate
floppy disk controller and the simultaneous operation of the video
emulation with 16 colors, may cause errors while writing or formatting
disks. The reason is the limited bandwidth of the original or
enhanced custom chipset of the Amiga. In this case it is necessary to
reduce the number of colors to 4 or 8.
This problem does not occur with the new AA chipset or a EGA/VGA card.


The backslash on the Amiga keyboard
-----------------------------------
The scancodes of the Amiga keyboard are not similar to those of a PC-AT
keyboard. Therefore not all characters are on the same keys than in
Amiga mode. Depending on the PC operating system, the backslash ´\´ key,
which is important for the PC mode, is available on the ALT+´\´ or right
Amiga + ´\´ keys.

NOTE: To get the backslash under Windows without problems (on the keys
      right Amiga + ´\´) it is necessary to choose 101-/102-keys
      AT-keyboard during the Windows installation. If the backslash is
      not available after your Windows installation, you can switch to
      the correct keyboard with the Windows SETUP program. SETUP starts
      form the DOS prompt or within a Windows session.


More computing power with  GoldenGate-486SLC/SLC2
-------------------------------------------------
You will have up to 20% more computing power with a GoldenGate-486SLC/486SLC2
if you start GG with the option FAST. This option must not be used if there
are ISA-cards in the pc-slots which can be isa-busmasters.



Kindest regards
The Vortex Team
@ENDNODE
