@NODE Questions_e "Common questions about Golden Gate Card"

              @{b} COMMON QUESTIONS ABOUT GOLDEN GATE CARD @{ub}

@{s}1. What's the actual version of the Goldmine I and II ?@{us}

The actual version of the Goldmine I is 1.31.27.-02/94 and Goldmine II is
1.04-08/93. This version contains the FAST mode that speep up at 10-20%.
You can get this update for free. If you send us two empty 3.5" disks, a
self adressed envelope and four international reply coupons.

At 24 July 1995, Further developments for the Golden Gate are not planned
at the moment.

@{s}2. Laplink doesn't work with the Golden Gate card. Why ?@{us}

Laplink works fine via the parallel port of a multi I/O adapter and the
parallel (centronics) port. Because the Laplink software programms the
RS232 hardware directly, there are problems with the data transfer.
We have tested the serial port emulation with Telemate, QModem and Procomm
without problems. Telemate and Qmodem are shareware programs.

@{s}3. Can you use fastram with the Amiga 4000 ?@{us}

You cannot use fastram on the amiga 4000 or fastram from a GVP accelerator
with the Golden Gate. This ram cannot be accessed via the 16 bit Zorro II
interface.

@{s}4.Problems come with Memaker. Why ?@{us}

We also encountered some problems with Memaker, depending on the configuration.
If you use the Amiga harddisk als PC partition, it is necessary to start
smartdrv.exe before you start emm386.exe in config.sys. Memaker does not know
this.

@{s}5. Why Golden Gate doesn't use correctly floppy disk drives ?@{us}

Golden Gate allows you to exchange the order of the floppy disk drives (e.g
FD1 as A: and FD0: as B:). As soon as you use the copy programs of backup
programs which do directly access to floppy controller hardware. you have to
map the drive exactly after the physical order (FD0 as drive A:, FD1 as
drive B:). You cannot use Amiga drives with such programs. After you have
correclty mapped the drives, your programs should accept them. We have
tested this with VGAcopy, MSBackup and CPBackup.

@{s}6. Can you use an Amiga CD-Rom from the Golden Gate ?@{us}

It is not possible to access an Amiga CD-ROM from the Golden Gate. You have to
use a PC-SCSI-adapter if you want to use the CD-ROM for the PC side.

@{s}7. There is a GURU Meditation 8000000b with a GVP Combo Card  @{us}

You must set the memory in the GVP board as 'extended' (if possible or start
the Golden Gate with the option 'chip'.)

@{s}8. Can I use 8 bits RAM with 3 chips on the GoldenGate card  @{us}

No , the new versions of RAM SIMM with 3 chips don't work with the Golden Gate
card. You must use the RAM SIMM with 9 chips even if there are not cheap.



@ENDNODE
