@NODE OS_e "What's OS on GoldenGate card ?"

Whe have tested the Golden Gate board with OS/2 Warp, LINUX Slackware and they
work fine. To use them, you need the followin PC hardware in your computer
system. LINUX, OS/2 cannot access the emulated harddisk, floppy disks or I/O
ports
    -(S)VGA card or other OS/2 compliant video card
    -PC IDE harddisk
    -PC floppy drive (no Amiga floppy in the GG Setup)
    -PC I/O board with RS232/Centronics port and a OS/2 compliant serial mouse

DOS, Windows 3.1, Windows 95 work fine with the emulated Amiga hardware
components. It is no real 32 bit operating system and therefore uses the
standard bios calls (supported by the Golden Gate AT bios) in most cases.

